From 5d9545c74ffc5b6083cf9ae743f1c8ce85e92e3f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: radhevrishi <radhev.232@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 26 May 2026 11:05:41 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] patch 0886: Indian news RSS - Moneycontrol + Business
 Standard + name-token search

User audit: Bliss GVS Pharma had multiple news headlines about a 43.3%
acquisition by Anupam Rasayan over the past 2-4 days (Moneycontrol,
Business Standard, BusinessLine, ICICI Direct, CNBC TV18, NDTV Profit
all carrying the story), but the Home Movers attribution showed
"sector-cluster transmission - 11/23 peers" for BLISSGVS instead of
the acquisition.

Root cause: every article uses "Bliss GVS" or "Bliss GVS Pharma" -
none contain the literal string "BLISSGVS". Google News full-text
search for "BLISSGVS" returns the small set of BSE/NSE filing summaries
that DO use the ticker, missing all the major outlets. Yahoo Finance
RSS is keyed on the ticker too.

Three fixes in this patch:

1. Added Moneycontrol RSS feeds (MCtopnews, business, marketreports)
   - broad latest-news streams, post-filtered by ticker+name tokens.
   Indian smallcap corporate-action coverage on Moneycontrol is
   actually quite comprehensive; we just have to look there.

2. Added Business Standard RSS feeds (markets, companies) with the
   same post-filter approach.

3. New deriveNameTokens() heuristic generates plausible name fragments
   from the ticker for post-filtering:
     BLISSGVS  -> ["blissgvs", "bliss gvs", "bliss"]
     MARKSANS  -> ["marksans", "marks ans", "marksans"]   (less useful)
     ASTRAMICRO-> ["astramicro", "astra micro", "astra"]
     ANUPAMRAS -> ["anupamras", "anupam ras", "anupam"]
   When the caller also supplies an explicit companyName, that name AND
   a suffix-stripped variant are added to the token set. So a row that
   has the user-uploaded company name "Bliss GVS Pharma" gets even
   better matching.

4. Second Google News query variant when no companyName is supplied:
   "<ticker> stock OR shares OR upper circuit" -- Google indexes the
   ticker even when the headline uses long-form, so this catches
   acquisition / upper-circuit news that includes ticker mentions in
   the body.

fetchIndianNews now runs FIVE parallel queries (Yahoo, Google primary,
Moneycontrol, Business Standard, Google alt) instead of two; dedupes
by normalized title; sorts newest first; same 8s timeout budget per
feed via the existing fetchText AbortController.

Expected outcome for BLISSGVS on next deploy: Moneycontrol post-filter
matches "bliss gvs" in "Bliss GVS hits 20% upper circuit as Anupam
Rasayan to acquire up to 43% stake for Rs 1,369 crore", classifier
matches ACQUISITION pattern from 0882, the row chip becomes
"acquires 43.3% stake in Bliss GVS Pharma" - the actual catalyst.
